==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[chimera]],'' from the {{L.}} ''[[chimaera]],'' from the {{Gr.}} (''chimaira''), which means ''she-goat.'' This term entered English around 1638.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}
# A [[figment]] of the [[imagination]]; [[fantastic]] (in the [[archaic]] sense).
# Inherently [[fantastic]].

